channel.title: Cache Editor Problem
channel.description:
So, i've been messing around with the 718/723 matrix server. Attempting to load new cache, with a lack of results. That's not the point though. I'm trying to use the cache editor but am presented with this error:
Exception in thread "main" java.io.FileNotFoundException: cache\main_file_cache. dat2 (The system cannot find the path specified) at java.io.RandomAccessFile.open(Native Method) at java.io.RandomAccessFile.<init>(Unknown Source) at java.io.RandomAccessFile.<init>(Unknown Source) at com.alex.store.Store.<init>(Store.java:34) at com.alex.store.Store.<init>(Store.java:28) at com.alex.tools.itemsDefsEditor.Application.main(Application.java:37) Press any key to continue . . .
Yes, I understand what it means. Although I'm not sure how to fix it. I have no idea why it can't find the Main statement.
Heres my run:
@echo off @title Fucking work this time @echo cache editor java -classpath bin; com.alex.tools.itemsDefsEditor.Application pause
Anyone have any suggestions?
